Raven Network Spec v1.0

PantheonOS / Money Bin / Atlas Kernel
Subtitle: Distributed Epistemics, Delta Monitoring, and Reality-Gated State Update

⸻

1. Purpose

Formalize the Raven Network as a distributed epistemics engine that:
	•	deploys multiple retrieval and sensing nodes across information space
	•	aggregates raw signal from diverse substrates
	•	measures change over time
	•	compresses outputs into invariants, deltas, and candidate updates
	•	gates updates through falsification and reality testing
	•	updates system state without collapsing into bias loops or narrative drift

The Raven Network is not a mystical oracle.
It is a distributed measurement, retrieval, and calibration layer.

⸻

2. Core Thesis

Ravens bring back signal.
Compression extracts structure.
The Pantheon decides whether the structure is worth believing.

In concise form:

observe -> retrieve -> aggregate -> compress -> gate -> update

⸻

3. Canonical Definition

Raven Network = a federation of distributed retrieval nodes that scan information environments, collect relevant deltas, and return them to a compression-and-gating core for epistemic update.

