6. Formal Components

Let:
	•	Q = active query, hypothesis, or watch-target
	•	R_i = Raven node i
	•	S_i(t) = signal returned by Raven i at time t
	•	A(t) = aggregated signal set at time t
	•	C(t) = compressed representation at time t
	•	G(C) = gating function
	•	U(t) = state update candidate
	•	SV(t) = StateVector at time t

Then:

6.1 Retrieval

A(t) = \bigcup_i R_i(Q, t)

6.2 Compression

C(t) = Compress(A(t), Memory, Invariants)

6.3 Gating

U(t) = G(C(t), Evidence, Falsifiers, Ethics)

6.4 State Update

SV(t+1) = SV(t) + U(t)

Only if U(t) passes threshold.

