8. Delta Monitoring

This is the sharp edge of the system.

8.1 Definition

A delta is not just new information.
A delta is a meaningful change in a tracked signal under known context.

\Delta S = S(t+1) - S(t)

8.2 Types of Deltas
	•	Novelty delta — new information enters
	•	Convergence delta — independent sources align
	•	Contradiction delta — previously aligned signal breaks
	•	Suppression delta — expected signal disappears
	•	Threshold delta — quantity becomes qualitatively different
	•	Rotation delta — same structure appears in another domain
	•	Reaction delta — system behavior changes in response to probe

8.3 Good Delta Criteria

A delta is worth tracking if it has at least one of:
	•	predictive relevance
	•	cross-domain repeatability
	•	anomaly strength
	•	structural novelty
	•	decision impact

