14. Phase Transition Detection

The system may monitor for nonlinear change, but must define it rigorously.

14.1 Grounded Definition

A phase transition is a discontinuous or threshold-dependent change in measurable system behavior.

14.2 Candidate Metrics
	•	sudden convergence across previously divergent agents
	•	abrupt jump in model capability
	•	new cross-domain transfer behavior
	•	sustained contradiction collapse
	•	nonlinear adoption curve

14.3 Rule

Do not call something a phase transition unless:
	•	baseline exists
	•	metric is defined
	•	discontinuity is measurable
	•	alternate explanations are tested

